kb:entity-sets
    pred:relates-to kb:meta-visual-generation ;
    pred:has-status "functional" ;
    pred:description "Two entry points to the same concept: (1) MULTI-ENTITY CREATION — define a 'set' up front (members + optional premade relating triples), a template you instantiate to drop a whole related cluster at once (e.g. a 'trip' set = 2 people + 2 options + routes, like the starter graph's shape). Lives alongside entity types. (2) MULTI-NODE GROUPING IN THE GRAPH — select several nodes (extends the existing Ctrl+click multi-select) and GROUP them; a grouped selection unlocks additional ANALYZE options (analyze the subgraph as a unit) and a 'save as entity set' action that captures the members + their inter-relationships as a reusable set. Grouping also feeds F58.5 asset-assembly (a set is a natural generation subgraph) and F60 arrange (a set is a natural page section)." ;
    pred:principle "Entity TYPES describe ONE node's kind; entity SETS describe a reusable GROUP of nodes + the relationships among them. A set is a customizable grouping — optionally with premade triples relating its members — that a user can define once and instantiate, the way types are reused." ;
    pred:remaining "FIRST CUT SHIPPED (2026-07-10): batch multi-select in the graph -> '⬡ group as set' creates a first-class ktype:EntitySet node linked to members via urn:kbase:predicate/has-member (src/lib/rdf/entity-sets.ts; rendered via the new EntitySet built-in type; deletion-protected as a group). Term 'set' used in the UI. REMAINING: (1) instantiate a set as a TEMPLATE (drop the whole cluster + premade relating triples up front); (2) selecting a set node highlights/re-selects its members; (3) extra ANALYZE options on a grouped selection; (4) less-clunky multi-select (the entry gesture is still canvas Ctrl+click)." ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:tested-by "src/lib/rdf/__tests__/entity-sets.test.ts" ;
    rdfs:label "Entity sets (multi-entity groupings)" ;
    pred:feature-id "F65" ;
    pred:relates-to kb:entity-types ;
    pred:relates-to kb:arrange-layout-builder ;
    pred:open-question "Storage: is a set a first-class node (ktype:EntitySet) whose members are linked by a 'has-member' predicate, or a saved selection/template? First-class node makes it queryable + shareable and round-trips in TTL." ;
    pred:priority "high" ;
    pred:relates-to kb:sets-xr .

kb:sets-xr
    pred:relates-to kb:int-game-engine ;
    pred:has-status "speculative" ;
    pred:part-of kb:entity-sets ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:feature-id "F65.1" ;
    pred:description "Consider VR/AR/XR as the premier UI/UX for sets: in an immersive 3D graph, batch-select by looking/pointing or a lasso volume, GRAB nodes and gather them with hand/controller gestures, and drop them into a set; manipulate, split, and re-arrange sets in space (ties to F59 spatial layout + F60 arrange). Builds on the existing VR/AR shells (F7, VRShell/ARShell + WebXR) and the game-engine option (F59.1) for richer spatial rendering. XR turns the clunky Ctrl+click multi-select into a direct, embodied action." ;
    pred:relates-to kb:spatial-force-layout ;
    rdfs:label "Sets in VR / AR / XR" ;
    pred:depends-on kb:vr-ar-shells ;
    pred:principle "Grouping nodes into a set is inherently SPATIAL — the natural gesture is to physically gather things. XR is where that becomes fluid: reach out, grab nodes, pull them into a pile, and that pile IS a set. It directly answers the 'multi-select is clunky' problem for sets." .

