    pred:depends-on kb:graph-publishing ;
    pred:has-status "planned" ;
    pred:priority "medium" ;
    pred:feature-id "F47" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:description "Make Shelly available inside the Sveltia editing experience so authors can draft, summarize, and refine page content grounded in the graph — without forking Sveltia. TWO CANDIDATE INTEGRATION PATHS (validate before building): (1) HOST-APP OVERLAY — Sveltia is already served in-app at /admin; embed it and render a Shelly panel in the surrounding Reckons.AI chrome, exchanging the current entry's text via postMessage / the File System Access working copy, so Sveltia's bundle is untouched; (2) REGISTRATION API — if Sveltia exposes Decap-style registerWidget / registerEditorComponent / registerPreviewTemplate hooks, mount a Shelly widget through config/init without patching source. Shelly reuses existing graph-grounded tools: kb_generate_page (draft a WebPage body from the graph via local Ollama), kb_entity_markdown (deterministic entity->markdown, no LLM), kb_compress (grounded context). Use cases: 'draft this page from the entity', 'summarize these triples', 'write the F46 question-context blurb'. Consent + safety: ETHICS_PREAMBLE applies; suggestions are proposals the author edits, never silent writes. Relates to the Shelly bridge (stores/shelly-bridge.svelte.ts), F27 publishing, and F46 question-context pages." ;
