kb:publish-safety-gate
    pred:has-status "planned" ;
    pred:part-of kb:content-safety ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:description "Before a graph is published to the open web (publishSiteToGitHub / any public target), run it through the same classifier (classifyStatement / filterBlockedStatements) and REFUSE to publish when blocked content is present — with a clear explanation, not a silent drop. Distinct from the existing export ADVISORY (which warns): the publish gate BLOCKS. Also leans on the natural barrier — Reckons.AI hosts nothing, so public publishing requires the user's OWN domain/hosting/file-sharing (Cloudflare, GitHub Pages, a Git host), which limits casual/anonymous abuse and makes the publisher accountable through their own provider. Builds on content-safety; extends site-export.ts." ;
    pred:feature-id "F66" ;
    pred:principle "PRIVATE sharing is the user's to manage (handing someone a .ttl is like emailing a file — the app doesn't police it). PUBLIC publishing to the open web is GATED: make a good-faith effort to block publicly sharing graphs that incite violence or are otherwise illegal or hateful." ;
    rdfs:label "Publish Safety Gate" ;
    pred:relates-to kb:graph-publishing .

