kb:review-attention
    rdfs:label "Review at Scale — spotlight the decisions" ;
    pred:feature-id "F53" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:description "Redesign the review surface around the attention budget: condense to a few decisions, promote conflicts/contested changes, quiet the uncontested, and flag tenure-driven drift on an established graph. Onboarding is this same problem at t=0 (see soft-onboarding). Relates to the review workbench (F30) and partial facts (F32)." ;
    pred:principle "Tenure anchors perspective. The longer a graph is worked, the more its established intention frames new facts — adding to an OLD graph pulls new triples toward the old view (drift). Surface that pull; adding fresh triples is not the same as extending an anchored graph." ;
    pred:principle "Spend attention on disagreement, not agreement. Fresh, uncontested facts should flow through quietly; CONFLICTS and DECISIONS get the spotlight." ;
    pred:priority "high" ;
    pred:relates-to kb:partial-facts ;
    pred:has-status "planned" ;
    pred:principle "Granularity breeds rubber-stamping. A review list that is too fine trains the human to 'accept all' — condense decisions to a manageable few at a time." ;
    pred:relates-to kb:review-workbench .

