kb:mobile-uiux
    pred:feature-id "F36" ;
    pred:description "Make Reckons.AI genuinely usable on mobile by fixing how the app uses its UI libraries. DIAGNOSIS (measured 2026-07-07): no shared breakpoint system — 23 hand-rolled @media blocks across ~10 arbitrary px breakpoints (600/640/500/900/380/420...) vs a single Tailwind responsive prefix; Tailwind v4 is installed but its responsive system is effectively unused; no useMediaQuery/viewport store and no @theme screens tokens. SnapPanel is a px-width position:fixed floating window dragged via MOUSE events (clientX/clientY, no touch) that snaps to corners computed from window.innerWidth — unusable on a phone. 18 fixed/absolute floating panels stacked by z-index (300-500) overlap instead of reflowing. bits-ui Dialog/Popover/Select/Tooltip are used as desktop patterns (center modals, hover tooltips) with no mobile sheet/drawer equivalent. ARCHITECTURE (phased): (1) FOUNDATION — one breakpoint source of truth: Tailwind @theme screens tokens + CSS custom-media + a Svelte 5 viewport rune store (isMobile / isTouch / breakpoint via matchMedia + pointer:coarse). (2) ADAPTIVE PRIMITIVES — a Sheet/Drawer primitive (bits-ui Dialog styled as a bottom sheet) and an AdaptivePanel wrapper that renders SnapPanel on desktop but a bottom sheet / full-screen drawer on mobile; Select -> sheet/native picker on mobile; Tooltip -> tap-to-reveal or dropped on coarse pointers. (3) INPUT — replace SnapPanel mouse-drag with Pointer Events (touch + mouse) and disable free-drag on mobile in favor of the sheet. (4) LAYOUT — single-column reflow below 640px, primary actions in the thumb zone, touch gestures on the 2D/3D graph, >= 44px targets. Verified by F34 deep tests against the mobile-tagged guidelines in kb:web-uiux-rubric (touch-targets, responsive-layout, progressive-disclosure). Prioritized over F35 steering-committee." ;
    rdfs:label "Mobile UI/UX Architecture" ;
    pred:relates-to kb:deep-testing ;
    pred:has-status "planned" ;
    pred:priority "high" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:depends-on kb:visual-testing .

