<urn:reckons:story/rm-step-1>
    rdf:type <urn:reckons:story/Step> ;
    <urn:reckons:story/content> "Reckons.AI is a personal knowledge graph that extracts semantic triples from anything you feed it -- notes, URLs, documents, repos, calendars. It runs entirely in your browser with zero cloud dependency. Knowledge stays local, private, and under your control." ;
    <urn:reckons:story/order> "1"^^xsd:integer ;
    <urn:reckons:story/title> "The Vision" ;
    <urn:reckons:story/partOf> <urn:reckons:story/roadmap-tour> ;
    <urn:reckons:story/highlight> kb:reckons-ai .

kb:n8n-cloud-sync
    pred:feature-id "F20" ;
    pred:principle "n8n is NOT a backend for all things Reckons.AI. It is an OPTIONAL, PER-USER automation layer: a user connects their OWN self-hosted n8n to enable personalized automation/integration flowing into AND out of their Reckons.AI. The app stays local-first with no general backend; n8n owns web side-effects, never core state. (Mirrored in CLAUDE.md → Integration Boundaries for coding agents.)" ;
    pred:has-workflow kb:n8n-sync-hub ;
    pred:has-status "functional" ;
    pred:has-workflow kb:n8n-source-monitor ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:has-use-case kb:n8n-contact-form ;
    rdfs:label "n8n Automation" ;
    pred:description "Route web integrations through a self-hosted n8n instance (open-source automation, no SaaS). The clean division of labour: the app stays static/offline-first and owns the VISUAL building; n8n owns the web side-effects (email, sheets, tickets, monitoring). settings.n8nBaseUrl (Settings → Integrations) points at the instance." ;
    pred:remaining "PARTIALLY WIRED (2026-07-10). DONE: Settings → Integrations n8nBaseUrl field, and the first end-to-end app use case — the contact form (kb:n8n-contact-form). STILL UNWIRED: graph upload/download via the Sync Hub webhooks, and currents register/pull via the Currents Monitor (F29.2) — the integration code exists (src/lib/integrations/n8n/currents-sync.ts) but nothing calls it from the app yet. Status scaffolded -> functional now that one real path works. Remaining: wire graph sync + currents, and verify against the live VPS." .

