kb:graph-zoom-to-fit
    pred:feature-id "F45" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:priority "low" ;
    pred:relates-to kb:knowledge-graph ;
    pred:description "A user SETTING that, when enabled, automatically zooms/pans the graph to fit all currently-visible nodes whenever the visible set changes due to a newly-applied force LAYOUT (free/focus/hub/time/order/tree) or a FILTER (status/source/type/no-type/no-source). Today the camera keeps its previous framing after such a change, so nodes can land off-screen or clustered until the user manually zooms. Scope: compute the bounding box of visible nodes after layout settle / filter apply and animate the 2D viewport transform (and the 3D camera) to frame it with padding; debounce so rapid filter toggling doesn't thrash; respect prefers-reduced-motion (snap, no animation); off by default (setting under graph/display) so it never fights users who curate their own framing. Relates to the graph rendering feature and the mobile reflow work (small viewports benefit most)." ;
    pred:relates-to kb:mobile-uiux ;
    rdfs:label "Auto Zoom-to-Fit on Layout / Filter Change" ;
    pred:has-status "planned" .

kb:content-safety
    pred:principle "Responsibility model: Reckons.AI is a neutral, local-first TOOL — the user owns and is responsible for the content they create and share. The app makes a good-faith EFFORT to protect users and keep the worst content off the public web, but is not responsible for user-generated content. Documented for humans in SAFETY.md (repo root)." ;
    pred:principle "Ethics AND morals, not just law. Laws vary across borders and legality is a floor, not a ceiling — Reckons.AI applies a baseline ethical standard (no incitement, no hate, no sexualization of minors) regardless of local legality. Some things simply should not be broadcast publicly." ;
    pred:has-part kb:verified-badge ;
    pred:has-part kb:publish-safety-gate ;
    pred:has-status "production" ;
    rdfs:label "Content Safety" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:description "Ethics preamble in all LLM prompts (ETHICS_PREAMBLE, src/lib/safety/content-policy.ts). Content classifier (blocked/mature/none) filters blocked content on ingest; mature is flagged. Export advisory headers warn recipients. Local-first: nothing leaves the device unless the user connects an integration." .

<urn:reckons:story/rm-step-2>
    <urn:reckons:story/title> "The Core Loop" ;
    <urn:reckons:story/highlight> kb:wf-review ;
    <urn:reckons:story/highlight> kb:wf-compare ;
    <urn:reckons:story/highlight> kb:wf-ingest ;
    <urn:reckons:story/highlight> kb:wf-explore ;
    <urn:reckons:story/partOf> <urn:reckons:story/roadmap-tour> ;
    rdf:type <urn:reckons:story/Step> ;
    <urn:reckons:story/content> "Five workflows form the backbone: Ingest (add knowledge), Review (curate with human-in-the-loop), Explore (navigate the graph), Compare (semantic diffs), and Reckon (AI-powered reasoning). Every triple passes through review before entering your confirmed graph." ;
    <urn:reckons:story/order> "2"^^xsd:integer ;
    <urn:reckons:story/highlight> kb:wf-reckon .

kb:integration-orchestration
    pred:open-question "How much orchestration lives IN Reckons.AI vs. delegated to n8n? Lean: model intent + simple schedules in-app, delegate complex multi-service flows to the user's n8n (its job), per the n8n-is-not-a-backend principle (F20)." ;
    pred:description "Let a user define trigger events, dependencies BETWEEN integration actions, and schedules — so cross-integration flows are explicit and ordered (publish-after-draft, post-then-notify, nightly-sync). Two layers: (a) the user's own n8n owns the heavy multi-step automation (its native strength); (b) the app models the intent — trigger/dependency/schedule as graph facts — and hands it to n8n or runs light in-app schedules. Scheduling exists in Claude Code routines (CronCreate/ScheduleWakeup) as a pattern; here it is user-facing, per-graph. Plugs into the Integration Plugin SDK (F61) so any plug-in exposes trigger/action hooks." ;
    pred:has-status "speculative" ;
    rdfs:label "Integration orchestration & scheduling" ;
    pred:feature-id "F64" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:principle "Integrations must be INTERCONNECTABLE, with clearly definable trigger events, dependencies, and schedules — not just fire-and-forget. Example: a blogger's web page publishes ONLY AFTER the Facebook post is drafted. Order and timing are first-class." ;
    pred:relates-to kb:n8n-cloud-sync ;
    pred:depends-on kb:integration-plugin-sdk .

