kb:currents-phase-3
    pred:depends-on kb:currents-phase-1 ;
    pred:description "Pod mode in the graph view: pending arrivals render translucent and drifting (reuse the ghost-graph rendering machinery) with accept/dismiss directly on the node; whale-themed accents. Currents settings UI on the graph management page: define currents, toggle entity types, set location. Context blocks: weather via Open-Meteo (free, no key), in-your-state-yesterday via location-filtered items. Daily briefing summarized via prefer-local Ollama. STARTED 2026-07-02: pod toggle (whale chip) on the graph page; arrival nodes (pending-only entities) render translucent with a drift-bob and sky-blue dashed halo in KnowledgeGraph2D. SHIPPED 2026-07-03: accept/dismiss actions on the node panel when pod mode is on and the selected node is an unaccepted arrival (setStatus→confirmed/rejected across all pending statements touching that node) — src/routes/(app)/+page.svelte, with a small additive onarrivalstatus callback exposed from KnowledgeGraph2D.svelte; currents settings UI on the /kb graph-management page — define/edit/remove currents (slug auto-derived from label), kind select (rss/url/topic), cadence, enabled toggle, entity-type gate as toggle chips (registered types from entity-types.svelte.ts; empty = all allowed), and a location field — src/routes/(app)/kb/+page.svelte, persisted via a new replaceCurrentsSettings() helper in src/lib/rdf/currents-persist.ts (diffs against existing urn:reckons:meta/currents/* statements: rejects removed entries, revives identical-but-previously-rejected entries, adds new ones; settings statements stay status confirmed); 6 unit tests on the pure diff function. REFINED 2026-07-04: the floating pod toggle chip was removed from the graph view (user feedback: disliked the button); pod view is now enabled via a '🐋 pod view' toggle in the currents section of the Graph tab (/kb), backed by a per-device localStorage preference (src/lib/stores/pod-view.svelte.ts, podViewEnabled/setPodViewEnabled). The graph view reads the shared store and shows a small read-only '🐋 pod' status indicator (not a button) when on. Rationale: pod is a currents feature, so its controls live with currents settings on the Graph tab. Remaining: context blocks (weather, in-your-state-yesterday) and the daily briefing summary." ;
    rdfs:label "F29.3 — The Pod view & settings UI" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Phase> ;
    pred:has-status "functional" ;
    pred:part-of kb:currents .

