kb:docs-pipeline
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:description "The docs knowledge graphs (static/starter-guide.ttl, the hub with hnav:order-sequenced leap nodes, plus the nine static/docs-*.ttl sub-graphs: triples-rdf, llm, use-cases, features, integrations-tech, tips-security, timeline-ecosystem, architecture, testing) are the source of truth for the 'generated' sections of the published /docs site. scripts/docs-pages.ts (npm run docs:pages) parses the TTLs with n3, turns each qualifying entity (any subject typed under urn:kbase:type/, excluding each sub-graph's urn:reckons:docs/nav/ back-to-hub stub) into a WebPage, and writes content/<section>/<slug>.md via pageToMarkdown — so the output round-trips through scripts/md-align.ts exactly like Sveltia-authored pages. Every generated page carries generated: \"docs-kb\" in its frontmatter (page:generated / PAGE_GENERATED in src/lib/rdf/page.ts); regeneration is idempotent and prunes any previously-generated file whose entity was removed from the TTLs, but never touches a file without that tag. An entity asserted in both the hub (a lightweight 'summary' stub, kept inline for the hub's own story/graph view) and a sub-graph (the fuller definition) is owned by the sub-graph; slugs are disambiguated by section suffix when two distinct entities share a local name across sections. Generated ~236 pages across 10 sections on first run." ;
    pred:has-status "functional" ;
    rdfs:label "Docs graph Publishing Pipeline" ;
    pred:part-of kb:graph-publishing ;
    pred:feature-id "F27.2" ;
    pred:tooling "CI (.github/workflows/kb-watch.yml) runs scripts/docs-pages.ts on every push/PR: pushes to main that produce a diff are committed back as github-actions[bot] ('docs: regenerate content from docs graphs'); PRs only report the drift in the job summary. The generator's own idempotency is the loop guard — a regeneration commit produces zero further diff, so it doesn't retrigger itself." ;
    pred:depends-on kb:webpage-entity .

