kb:workspace-index
    pred:description "A top-level index .ttl at the workspace root that references every synced graph and sidecar file (local OR cloud) in Turtle form — a manifest of the folder's contents. With it, a Reckons.AI browser session and a set of synced files (local folder or Google Drive) can recover the FILE SESSION: reopen exactly the graphs, assets, and view that were active, rather than re-linking each graph by hand. The index is itself a graph (files/graphs as entities with paths, stable IDs, last-synced timestamps), so it round-trips like everything else and stays diffable." ;
    pred:feature-id "F57" ;
    pred:has-status "planned" ;
    rdfs:label "Workspace index + session recovery" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:relates-to kb:drive-folder-sync ;
    pred:depends-on kb:workspace-sync .

