    pred:description "Sync the workspace to a (shareable) Google Drive folder — the cloud sibling of local folder sync. Two-way: push each KB out as {name}.ttl and pull .ttl files back, reconciling new graphs and updating changed ones through the SHARED kb-import reconcile (src/lib/stores/kb-import.ts, extracted so local + Drive sync behave identically), with a content-hash loop guard. Uses the drive.file OAuth scope (only app-owned files). Store: src/lib/stores/drive-sync.svelte.ts; Drive folder ops (ensureFolder/listFolderTurtles/uploadTurtleToFolder) added to integrations/google/drive.ts; controls in the graph menu's graph-package panel (☁ sync to Google Drive / resync / unlink / auto-sync). Auto-sync (opt-in): debounced auto-push on every KB mutation (hooked into kb.svelte alongside the local export) + ~45s background poll for cloud pulls, with silent token refresh (bails instead of popping a consent dialog on a timer). Binary sidecar assets (preview blobs, GLB models, icon blobs) round-trip too — pushed into a shared Drive assets/ subfolder with KB-scoped filenames ({stem}__{category}__{file}) and pulled back via the TTL's asset refs. Feature-complete for graphs + assets; further polish (per-KB Drive subfolders, conflict UI) is optional." ;
