    pred:description "Iterate on the visual design of the published pages (F27 WebPage entities → content/*.md → prerendered /docs, editable via Sveltia CMS). Better page/layout templates, typographic rhythm, and section components — a lot of the product's visible output is these pages. Grounded in kb:web-uiux-rubric (visual hierarchy, legibility, readable-output) and evaluated by F34 deep tests (text + visual surfaces, device matrix). Because docs pages are generated from the graph (scripts/docs-pages.ts, no md→TTL back-prop), template/layout changes live in the generator + page.ts, not hand-edited markdown." ;
    pred:feature-id "F38" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> .

kb:offline-align-review
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    rdfs:label "Offline Alignment-Review Job" ;
    pred:in-dev "2026-07-08"^^xsd:date ;
    pred:feature-id "F41" ;
    pred:description "Offline jobs that review alignment/drift warnings in depth and propose graph changes for human review (never silent edits). DETERMINISTIC LAYER (functional): scripts/branch-align.ts --suggest turns each 'functional but untracked' drift into a pending suggestion in knowledge.pending.jsonl — features with kpred:remaining → propose in-dev; finished ones → propose in-production + a functional→production status-update; idempotent (dedup by subject+predicate+object); wired into npm run offline:sweep. FUTURE AGENT LAYER (planned): when OLLAMA_BASE_URL is set, a LOCAL model reads each flagged feature's triples + recent git and reasons about the correct env/status/proposal, grounded and emitted as a suggestion (ground-first + validate + emit-question, per the devstral salvage lesson). Extends the F33 pipeline and the offline procedures." ;
    pred:has-status "functional" ;
    pred:relates-to kb:release-pipeline .

